# CAD Annotation Samples — FreeCAD

Mechanical assembly annotation work produced using FreeCAD for AI training data pipelines.

## Overview
This repository contains annotated 3D mechanical assembly files created in FreeCAD. Components including shafts, gears, joints, and fasteners are labelled with structured metadata to support AI part-recognition model training.

## Tools Used
- FreeCAD 0.21
- Part Design & Assembly workbenches
- Manual annotation with structured label schema

## Annotation Schema
| Label | Description |
|-------|-------------|
| `SHAFT_xx` | Rotational shaft components |
| `GEAR_xx` | Gear and sprocket elements |
| `JOINT_xx` | Connection and fastener points |
| `ASSEMBLY_vx` | Full assembly version tag |

## Sample Output
